hopobject.body: Another service? it administration of methotrexate But Nov. 1, not Oct. 17, may be the real default date. That’s when $67 billion in payments to Social Security recipients, members of the military, retirees, and Medicare providers come due. “November 1 is really the doomsday date,” says former trader and economist Stephen Guilfoyle, echoing the view of many money managers. “But just the shock to the faith and credit of the U.S. government, I think the damage to the reputation will be done if it goes past Thursday.”
